Class AbstractSubSystem

    Checkable, ComponentElement, IdentHolder, ModelElement, Writeable, DecoratedBean, java.lang.Cloneable, javax.swing.undo.StateEditable
    public abstract class AbstractSubSystem
extends AbstractBeanComponent
implements IdentHolder, Writeable, DecoratedBean
    The base class for CAFEAN supported "sub system" groupings of components.

      • userDelete

        public javax.swing.undo.UndoableEdit userDelete​(java.util.List context)
        Description copied from class: AbstractComponent
        Performs all additional operations required in order to properly delete this component from its model. This will not be called for Connection type components as they can be handled in userDisconnect

        This empty base implementation is sufficient for nearly all components and simply returns null.

        In some plug-in specific cases other components may require notification that this component is about to be deleted by the user. In these cases an UndoableEdit for the changes to these components should be returned by this method.

        NOTE: This method does not handle the creation of the UndoableDelete for this component and serves only as a point of entry for additional undoable operations to be performed.

        Overrides:
        userDelete in class AbstractComponent
        Parameters:
        context - a List initially containing the components being deleted. Additional objects can be added to this list for use by subsequent components inside their userDelete methods.
        Returns:
        an UndoableEdit capable of undoing the additional required operations. This returned edit will be added to the deletion's CompoundEdit just before the UndoableDelete that includes this component.
        See Also:
        AbstractComponent.removeVerify(), UndoableDelete

      • reconnectImage

        public void reconnectImage​(java.util.Vector sourceComps,
                           java.util.Vector destComps)
        Reconnects the internal linkage of this component not handled by reconnectIdentReferences and rebuildConnections during a copy and/or paste operation.

        This method is called on the source component and is intended to rebuild appropriate structures for the destination component. (likely found by the destination's DB_ID matching the source's ident)/.

        reconnectImage in class AbstractComponent
        Parameters:

      • reconnectIdentReferences

        public void reconnectIdentReferences​(boolean preserveUnresolved,
                                     boolean useDbId)
        Description copied from class: GenericObject
        Resets this component's internal ident references to refer to appropriate components in the current AbstractModel. Intended for use after adding a component to a model and thus it's DB_ID will have been set to it's ident in the previous model. For ident references use find__ByDbId to find the new component, then store it's ident.

        Note: If this component's DB_ID is 0 this method does nothing.

        Specified by:
        reconnectIdentReferences in interface IdentHolder
        Overrides:
        reconnectIdentReferences in class AbstractComponent
        Parameters:
        preserveUnresolved - if true, ident references that aren't resolvable will be left dangling, if false, they will be set to 0.
        useDbId - if true, ident references will be reconnected via find_x_ByDB_ID; if false, ident references will be reconnected via find_x_ByIdent

      • drop

        public boolean drop​(java.awt.dnd.DropTargetDropEvent dtde,
                    java.awt.dnd.DropTarget target)
        Description copied from class: AbstractComponent
        Provides custom drop action for this component when adding the component to a drawn view. For example when a sub-system is dragged from the navigator into a view, it adds all of the elements of the subsystem into the view instead of creating a drawn representation of the subsystem. This can open user interfaces for controlling the insertion if desired. The DropTarget will have the DrawnView.
        Overrides:
        drop in class AbstractComponent
        Parameters:
        dtde - the DropTargetDropEvent
        target - the DropTarget which received the DropTargetDropEvent
        Returns:
        the boolean true if a custom drop event is provided

      • createSubsystemMenu

        public static javax.swing.JMenuItem createSubsystemMenu​(AbstractModel model,
                                                        java.util.List<AbstractComponent> components)
        Creates a menu intended for us as a sub-menu of the pop-up menu for the given list of selected components. This menu is the "Add To Sub-System" menu which contains an entry for each available sub-system in the model narrowed by the selected components being in a single sub-system. This menu also includes a "New" menu item for creating a new sub-system to contain the selected components.
        Parameters:
        model - the AbstractModel containing the given list of components.
        components - the List<AbstractComponent> of components for which to create a menu
        Returns:
        a JMenu created by this call containing the requested items
